### Description

When a component instance is used in content projection to call `close` method for hiding content, the `animate.leave` does not work. However, binding to the `close` method in the component host is effective.


```
@Component({
  selector: "overlay",
  template: `
  @if(opened()) { 
    <div style="width: 400px; height: 400px;" animate.enter="enter-animation" animate.leave="leave-animation"><ng-content /></div> 
  }`,
  styles: [`
.enter-animation { animation: slide 1s, fade 1s; }
.leave-animation { animation: slide 1s reverse, fade 1s reverse; }
@keyframes fade {
  from {opacity: 0;	}
  to {opacity: 1;	}
}
@keyframes slide {
  from { transform: translateY(20px); }
  to { transform: translateY(0); }
}
  `],
  host: {
    "(click)": "close()"
  }
})
export class Overlay {
  readonly opened = model<boolean>(false);
  open() {
    this.opened.set(true);
  }
  close() {
    this.opened.set(false);
  }
}
```

```
<overlay #overlay_>
<button type="button" (click)="overlay_.close(); $event.stopPropagation();">Close</button> <!-- animate.leave not work -->
</overlay>
```

